\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b 7-9}). {\b A. novi-belgii} group. Perennial 20-200 cm. Stem erect, often purplish, glabrous or with hairs in longitudinal bands. Leaves ovate to linear-lanceolate, with auriculate base, remotely toothed. Involucral bracts in several rows, acute. Ligules at least 1·5 mm wide.
