\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. A. non-belgii} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 877 (1753) ({\i A. brumalis} Nees). Stem 40-120 cm. Leaves ovate-lanceolate to linear-lanceolate, (3-)4-10 times as long as wide, auriculate at base, remotely toothed. Capitula in a symmetrical, sometimes corymbiform, panicle. Involucral bracts acute, the longest 5·5-7 mm, the outer as long as the inner and largely herbaceous, lax or with a recurved apex, shortly tapered. Ligules at least 1·5 mm wide, violet-blue or (in cultivars) white, violet or purple.{\i  In fens and on river-banks and railway-banks; also occurring on waste ground. Widely naturalized in C. & N.W. Europe.} [Au Be Br Cz Da Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hu It Ju No Po Rm ?Rs Su.] ({\i North America}.)
