\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. A.} × {\b salignus} Willd., {\i Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}: 2040 (1803) ({\i A. lanceolatus} × {\i novi-belgii}). Like {\b 7} but the leaves sometimes not or scarcely auriculate; outer involucral bracts not, or less distinctly, lax, enlarged and herbaceous; ligules light violet-blue. {\i River-banks, railway-banks and waste places. Widely naturalized, mainly in N. & C. Europe.} [Au Be Br Cz Da Fe Ga Ge He Ho Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W) Su.] ({\i Garden origin}.)
